  "callouts": [
    {
      "byline": "18 Years at the Grammys",
      "text": "JRM has managed security operations for the Grammy Awards for 18 consecutive years, most recently for the 68th Grammy Awards at Crypto.com Arena — trusted with one of music's biggest nights, year after year.",
      "author": "JRM Marketing"
    },
    {
      "byline": "12 Years at the Golden Globes",
      "text": "JRM proudly completed its 12th consecutive year providing security for the Golden Globe Awards at the Beverly Hilton, continuing a trusted partnership built on precision and discretion.",
      "author": "JRM Marketing"
    },
    {
      "byline": "16 Years with BET",
      "text": "Our partnership with BET spans 16 years, most recently securing the NAACP Image Awards at the Pasadena Civic Auditorium and the Image Awards at the Shrine Auditorium — thank you for trusting JRM.",
      "author": "JRM Marketing"
    },
    {
      "byline": "Giving Back to Our Communities",
      "text": "One of the most gratifying parts of our work is investing in our communities and schools. Thank you to every School Resource Officer nationwide protecting our most precious assets.",
      "author": "JRM Marketing"
    },
    {
      "byline": "Honoring Harry McKillop's Legacy",
      "text": "JRM is proud to carry forward Harry McKillop's lifetime of selfless service — a legacy honored by President Bush with the Secretary of Defense Medal of Exceptional Public Service.",
      "author": "JRM Marketing"
    },
    {
      "byline": "Next-Generation Emergency Response",
      "text": "JRM has partnered with Titan HST, a leading provider of next-generation emergency-response systems, to strengthen safety at live television events nationwide.",
      "author": "JRM Marketing"
    },
    {
      "byline": "6 Major Events, 2 Weeks",
      "text": "Our LA events team recently pulled off six major productions in just two weeks — a testament to the planning, teamwork, and readiness behind every JRM deployment.",
      "author": "JRM Marketing"
    },
    {
      "byline": "On the Ground at Comic-Con",
      "text": "From red carpets to convention floors, JRM's team brings the same standard of readiness to every environment — including securing one of the world's largest fan events, Comic-Con.",
      "author": "JRM Marketing"
    },
    {
      "byline": "Hip Hop's 50th, Coast to Coast",
      "text": "JRM's team supported Hip Hop's 50th anniversary celebration at Marquee New York alongside Tao Group and Apple — proof that our reach extends well beyond Los Angeles.",
      "author": "JRM Marketing"
    },
    {
      "byline": "Founded on 40 Years of Experience",
      "text": "S&S Labor Force, dba JRM, was built on President John McKillop's 40-year career in law enforcement and private security — a foundation that still guides every event we protect today.",
      "author": "JRM Marketing"
    }
  ],
  "team": [
    {
      "name": "John McKillop",
      "title": "CEO & President",
      "bio": "John has over 40 years of experience related to law enforcement and private industry security management.  John’s law enforcement career spanned 20 years of overseeing high level investigations relating to organized crime, gang activity and ended his career supervising the Robbery-Homicide division.  In 2002 he was awarded the honor of being one the top police officer awards in the international law enforcement community by the International Association of Chiefs of Police ( IACP) for his work overseeing and successful prosecution of one of the nation’s most prolific serial killers.\n\nAfter his law enforcement career John has been serving the private industry and has specialized in entertainment security.  John has been instrumental in creating and implementing security plans for some of the nations largest annual events such as Grammys, Emmys, Billboard Awards, American Music Awards and more.  As CEO and President of S&S Labor Force Inc. Dba JRM, John and his executive team have created a diverse portfolio of security services and is now one of the largest privately owned security companies in the region operating in major markets in the U.S. and other countries.",
      "photo": null
    },
    {
      "name": "Mike Izquierdo",
      "title": "COO",
      "bio": "Michael is a retired law enforcement officer from Southern California.  He brings over 30 years of law enforcement and security experience to the table.  His law enforcement career helped shape his critical thinking skills and strong tactical and analytical skills.  Michael is based out of our Las Vegas, NV office.  He has direct oversight of our national operations and branch offices.  His responsibilities include carrying out the strategic goals set by our CEO and Board of Directors.  He works closely with the V.P’s of the company to set our strategy and goals for business growth and development and to look out for the financial health of our company.  Working alongside our CEO, Michael has helped the company become the best and largest live broadcast security company in the U.S. ",
      "photo": "assets/synced/recAgQThuYKvrO5Gr-attRY8OFAJhXz9TDp.jpeg"
    },
    {
      "name": "Robert Paul Schwartz",
      "title": "CFO",
      "bio": "Results-orientated accounting professional with broad experience in a deadline-driven environment. Proven track record in consistently and effectively delivering accounting services that enhance the company's purpose and profitability. Strong technical accounting, tax and computer skills. Excellent research and financial analysis abilities. In-depth management reporting.Developing and implementing financial systems and controls. Budgeting and forecasting. Facilitation of internal and external auditing procedures. Regulatory compliance. Staff management and development. In-depth knowledge of accounting regulations and standards. Robert is an active Certified Public Accountant in California and Oregon with over 40 years of accounting experience. Robert has also held positions as Controller and Chief Financial Officer for a variety of privately held companies.",
      "photo": null
    },
    {
      "name": "Andy Sanders",
      "title": "Chief of Staff",
      "bio": "Andy has 20 years’ experience in event security and facility protection with a specialty in venue ingress and weapons detection technology.  His current role capitalizes on his extensive experience in Corporate America and has him oversee a vast portfolio of projects and company wide initiatives.  Andy is responsible for managing the day-to-day operations of the executive office and serving as a trusted advisor to the CEO. His ability to anticipate needs and proactively address challenges allows her to streamline processes, optimize resources, and drive efficient decision-making.",
      "photo": null
    },
    {
      "name": "Sean McKillop",
      "title": "SVP - Global Events & Development ",
      "bio": "Sean is a highly accomplished and dynamic individual serving as the Vice President of Business Development. With over a decade of experience in the corporate world, he has established himself as a strategic leader in driving growth and forging successful partnerships. His impressive track record includes successfully spearheading numerous business initiatives and expansion projects across the globe. Known for his exceptional networking skills, he has a knack for identifying new opportunities and cultivating strong relationships with key stakeholders. As Vice President of Business Development, Sean is responsible for envisioning and executing innovative strategies to expand the company's market presence and drive revenue growth. Leveraging his deep understanding of market trends and customer needs, he plays a pivotal role in shaping the organization's long-term growth trajectory.",
      "photo": "assets/synced/recm9g2u87RkDnOT8-att3VyoJVmhsJ2WZ6.jpeg"
    },
    {
      "name": "Tony D'Gracia",
      "title": "EVP - Northeast Operations",
      "bio": "Drawing on more than two decades of distinguished experience in law enforcement, investigations, and high-level security operations, Tony brings unparalleled expertise and strategic insight to the private security sector. During his extensive career in law enforcement and the private sector, Tony honed critical skills in tactical response, threat assessment, crisis management, and complex investigations. This foundation in public safety provided a deep understanding of proactive security measures and regulatory compliance that few in the private sector can match. Tony obtained a Bachelor’s degree in Criminal Justice from John Jay College of Criminal Justice, and holds multiple certifications including Certified Fraud Examiner (CFE) and NYS Security Guard Instructor.",
      "photo": null
    },
    {
      "name": "Sevan Ohanians",
      "title": "VP - Event Operations",
      "bio": "Sevan Ohanians is an action-oriented and result-focused professional, offering 20+ years of experience in project management and operations management in fast paced environments. An expert in organization, completion, and project follow through. Extensive experience in managing high-profile clientele, risk assessment, and threat mitigation and leads our Events team on the West Coast. Sevan’s creative thinking and analytical mindset enable him to identify untapped markets and develop tailored solutions to meet customer demands. He thrives on building high-performing teams, fostering a collaborative work environment, and empowering his colleagues to achieve their full potential.",
      "photo": "assets/synced/recgwu8yzDURNivqR-attCOmQkPofl3YbJB.jpeg"
    }
  ],
